          <span class="pub-number">001</span>
          <div class="pub-title">An Investigation of MMR‐Related Mumps Cluster Following Immunization Among Practical Nursing Students, Bangkok, Thailand, 2024</div>
          <div class="pub-journal">Journal of Tropical Medicine (Wiley) · Aug 1, 2025</div>
          <div class="pub-doi">DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1155/jotm/9974081" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">10.1155/jotm/9974081</a></div>
          <details>
            <summary>Show detail</summary>
            <p class="pub-contributors"><strong>Contributors:</strong> Sethapong Lertsakulbunlue, Drunphob Srithammavong, Kamonchanok Tepsittha, Hataya Kanjanasombut, Vitchakorn Poonyakanok, Viravarn Luvira, Phimphan Pisutsan, Rachata Charoenwisedsil, Pathomthep Leowattana, Peeriya Watakulsin et al.</p>
            <p class="pub-abstract">This study investigated a cluster of mumps-like cases among practical nursing students following MMR vaccination, identifying operational risk factors and confirming vaccine-related mumps infections through molecular analysis. Recommendations were made to improve vaccination campaign processes.</p>
          </details>
